page.title: 06REFRESHMENTS AT HIGH BEECH.
page.content: Next to the Kings Oak pub is a takeaway food shop.The lady has been working there for 2 years,she enjoys her job very much.Buisness starts around 10.30am and closes when buisness stops. The buisiest day is Sunday at about 12pm. They sell hot and cold food like sausage rolls,sandwiches,rolls and ice- creams.They also open in winter.It is very busy in summer and tourists go there.They come from many countries but mostly France and Germany. There is no vandalism around this area and bikes are not allowed close to the shop. They have not noticed any changes around the forest,except for there being more litter.
